Electrons
---------

- N physical electrons will be represented by 1 model electron
- each model electron will have the following characteristics
  - position: x,r,z,r^2
  - velocity: vx,vy,vz
- each model interval:
  - a quantity of model electrons will be released from the grid each dt,
    - initial position is slightly inside or outside the grid
    - initial velocity is XXX 
  - each model electron will do one of the following:
    - based on the D ion characteristics at the location, the model electron
      may be absorbed by a model D ion, causing:
      . the model D ion to become a model D atom
      . the model electron is removed 
    - based on the D atom characteristics at the location, the model electron
      may ionize the D atom, causing:
      . the model D ataom to become a model D ion
      . the creation of another model D electron
      . the velocity of the existing and new electrons will be determined based
        on conservation of energy and momemtum
    - have its velocity and position updated based on current position, velocity, 
      and electric field
  - if a model electron's updated position is outside the chamber then
    - this model electron will be removed f
    - it will be tabulated to keep track of the current leaving the chamber
      and the velocity profile of the electrons that strike the chamber wall

Electric Field
--------------

- Spherical symetry assumption, so field direction is radial, and strength
  is the same for all positions in the chamber of the same radius
- The last step of each model interval will recompute the electric field
  strength, at each radius interval. The quantity of ions, electrons, and
  the electric field of the grid will be used to calculate the field strength.



